The '''MCW Rage Television Championship''' is a [[professional wrestling]] [[professional wrestling championship#Gimmick/style championships|television]] [[professional wrestling championship|championship]] owned by the [[MCW Pro Wrestling]] (MCW) [[professional wrestling promotion|promotion]]. The title was created and debuted on February 21, 2001 at a MCW [[House show|live event]].

The inaugural champion was Gregory Martin, who defeated Ronnie Zukko in the finals of a tournament to win the championship on February 21, 2001 at an MCW live event.

The current champion is [[Ryan McBride]], who is in his second reign.

