{{Infobox video game |title=Strength of the Sword 3 |image=Blardy Blar Blarrrr Ivent Games 1.jpg |developer=Ivent Games |publisher=Ivent Games |designer=Lyubomir Iliev |programmer=Gerogi Rakidov |released= '''PlayStation 3''' {{vgrelease|NA|December 10, 2013|EU|June 5, 2013<ref name="press">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/193473/STRENGTH_OF_THE_SWORD_3_FOR_PSNPS3.php|title=Official Press Release}}</ref>}} '''Microsoft Windows''', '''Linux''', '''PlayStation 4''', '''PlayStation Vita''', '''Wii U'''{{vgrelease|WW|TBA}} |modes=[[Single player]] |genre=[[Action game|Action]], [[hack and slash]] |series= |engine=[[PhyreEngine]] |platforms=[[PlayStation 3]]<ref name="video">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kHnK6fUDi5I|title=Official Preview Video}}</ref> [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Linux]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[PlayStation Vita]], [[Wii U]] }}
'''''Strength of the Sword 3''''' (re-released as '''''Strength of the Sword Ultimate''''') is a third-person, fast-paced, challenge driven, action beat 'em up video game set in a fantasy realm. The game is produced by the small indie game studio Ivent Games for [[PlayStation 3]], with updated versions planned for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Linux]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[PlayStation Vita]] and [[Wii U]]. The story focuses around Strahil, the former leader of the "Upper Kingdom" and the victim of a cruel plot that led to his imprisonment in a dark cave. As Strahil, you will have to advance through four different locations set on the "Island of Dreams" and seek vengeance from the evil figures behind the plot that led to his imprisonment. Throughout his way Strahil will have to deal with brutal enemies who would prefer to die rather than surrender.
Originally a [[PlayStation Network]] exclusive, it was released in Europe on June 5, 2013, and December 10, 2013, in North America for PlayStation 3, a Kickstarter campaign in 2015 received the funding to bring the game to more platforms.
==Reception== {{Video game reviews | MC = 67/100<ref name=MC/> | GSpot = 6/10<ref name=GSpot>{{Cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/strength-of-the-sword-3-review/1900-6415613/ |title=Strength of the Sword 3 Review |publisher=[[GameSpot]] |last=Kemps |first=Heidi |date=20 December 2013 |accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref> | rev1 = ''[[PlayStation Universe]]'' | rev1Score = 7/10<ref name=PSU>{{Cite web |url=https://www.psu.com/reviews/strength-of-the-sword-3-review-an-ambitious-title-from-indie-dev-ivent/ |title=Strength of the Sword 3 review: an ambitious title from indie dev Ivent |publisher=[[PlayStation Universe]] |last=Shillabeer-Hill |first=Benjamin |date=29 June 2013 |accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref> }}
''Strength of the Sword 3'' received mixed reviews from critics upon release. On [[Metacritic]], the game holds a score of 67/100 based on 15 reviews, indicating "mixed or average reviews."<ref name=MC>{{Cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/strength-of-the-sword-3 |title=Strength of the Sword 3 for PlayStation 3 Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref>
