{{inline|date=February 2017}}{{primarysources|date=February 2017}}
The '''U.S. National Water Ski Championships''' is an annual [[Water skiing|water ski]] competition that has taken place since 1939. Hosted by the American Water Ski Association (AWSA) and taking place every year since its inception, with the exception of 1942-1945, the competition is the oldest and longest-running water ski competition in the world. The U.S. Nationals is one of the sport's three major championships along with the [[Water Ski World Championships]] (since 1949), and the [[Masters Water Ski Tournament]] (since 1959).

