{{unreferenced|date=October 2016}}
In Hindi literature, '''Vyangya''' means satire. Vyangya writings includes the essence of sarcasm and humour in Hindi literature. 
Some of the better known writers in this genre are [[Harishankar Parsai]], [[Sri Lal Sukla]], [[K. P. Saxena]],[[Gyan Chaturvedi]], [[Suryakumar Pandey]], [[Sharad Joshi]], etc.



